NOTE:  It is possible to use Traefik with ACME (Lets Encrypt).  This will require modification beyond the scope of this template (although you could modify the traefik.toml pretty easily to enable this).

HOW TO PROXY OTHER APPS:&#xD;
Traefik uses labels to decide what to proxy and where to send requests.&#xD;
Here are the labels available.&#xD;  
traefik.enable=true #required: add this label to the container you want to proxy&#xD;
traefik.backend=plexstats #name of the container required:(ie tautulli)&#xD;
traefik.frontend.rule=Host:plexstats.domain.fun required: (change to your subdomain and domain name)&#xD;
traefik.frontend.rule=Host:domain.fun; PathPrefix: /plexstats #optional: not needed unless using subfolders vs subdomains&#xD;
traefik.port=8181 #required: the port the container listens on (source port, not the port mapping in unraid)&#xD;
traefik.docker.network=bridge #required&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.SSLRedirect=true #optional: redirect http to https, might as well use it&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.STSSeconds=315360000 #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.browserXSSFilter=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.contentTypeNosniff=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.forceSTSHeader=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.SSLHost=domain.fun #required: set to your domain name&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.STSIncludeSubdomains=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.STSPreload=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.headers.frameDeny=true #optional&#xD;
traefik.frontend.auth.basic.usersFile=/shared/.htpasswd #optional: set this label to use the /shared/.htpasswd for basic auth

